			<Set PolicyBranchType="POLICY_BRANCH_HONOR"/>
		</Update>
	</Buildings>
	<Language_en_US>
		<Delete Tag="TXT_KEY_POLICY_BRANCH_HONOR_HELP" />
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_POLICY_BRANCH_HONOR_HELP">
			<Text>[COLOR_POSITIVE_TEXT]Honor[ENDCOLOR] improves the effectiveness of one's army in a variety of ways.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Adopting Honor gives a +33% combat bonus VS Barbarians, and notifications will be provided when new Barbarian Encampments spawn in revealed territory. Gain [ICON_CULTURE] Culture for the empire for each enemy unit killed. Unlocks building the Temple of Artemis.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Adopting all policies in the Honor tree will grant [ICON_RESEARCH] Science for each enemy unit killed. A Great General appears outside the [ICON_CAPITAL] Capital. Great Generals are earned twice as fast, have +2 [ICON_MOVES] Movement, and can be purchased with [ICON_PEACE] Faith starting in the Industrial Era.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Update>
			<Set Text="All units gain +15% [ICON_STRENGTH] combat strength when attacking cities." />
			<Where Tag="TXT_KEY_WONDER_STATUE_ZEUS_HELP" />
		</Update>
		<Update>
			<Set Text="Requires Honor. +10% [ICON_FOOD] Growth in all cities. +15% [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production when building ranged units." />
			<Where Tag="TXT_KEY_WONDER_TEMPLE_ARTEMIS_HELP" />
		</Update>
	</Language_en_US>


